cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.LG 

The paper deals with the recognition of sign language using deep learning architectures and multimodal data, including skeletal and RGB video data. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the study aims to improve accessibility for digital assistants, which falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the use of deep learning architectures for sign language recognition also falls under machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
